Vice President Mike Pence visited Caterpillar, Inc. in Green Valley, Arizona, to speak about the importance of passing the U.S.-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA). He emphasized the economic benefits of the agreement, including job creation and increased wages for American workers. Pence urged the audience to reach out to their representatives in Congress and express their support for the USMCA. He also praised the success of Caterpillar as a legendary American company and highlighted the contributions of veterans in the workforce. Pence concluded by promising to continue fighting for the prosperity and safety of the nation.